* at a platform-specific path:\\n     8→  - macOS: `~/Library/Application Support/kiro-cli/data.sqlite3`\\n     9→  - Linux (CI): `~/.local/share/kiro-cli/data.sqlite3`\\n    10→- The `auth_kv` table has two rows needed for auth:\\n    11→  - `kirocli:odic:device-registration` — OAuth client registration (client_id, client_secret, etc.)\\n    12→  - `kirocli:odic:token` — access/refresh tokens with expiry\\n    13→- The `migrations` table must also be populated (kiro-cli-chat may refuse to use a DB without migration records)\\n    14→- `kiro-cli-chat whoami -f json` validates auth is working\\n    15→\\n    16→## Changes\\n    17→\\n    18→### 1. Both workflows — replace \\\"Inject Kiro auth token\\\" step\\n    19→\\n    20→Replace the current step that writes to `~/.aws/sso/cache/` with one that creates the SQLite database:\\n    21→\\n    22→```yaml\\n    23→- name: Inject Kiro auth token\\n    24→  if: <agent> == 'kiro'\\n    25→  run: |\\n    26→    mkdir -p ~/.local/share/kiro-cli\\n    27→    DB_PATH=\\\"$HOME/.local/share/kiro-cli/data.sqlite3\\\"\\n    28→    sqlite3 \\\"$DB_PATH\\\" <<'SQL'\\n    29→    CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS migrations (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY, version INTEGER NOT NULL, migration_time INTEGER NOT NULL);\\n    30→    INSERT OR IGNORE INTO migrations (id, version, migration_time) VALUES (1,0,0),(2,1,0),(3,2,0),(4,3,0),(5,4,0),(6,5,0),(7,6,0),(8,7,0),(9,8,0);\\n    31→    CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS auth_kv (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, value TEXT);\\n    32→    CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS state (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, value BLOB);\\n    33→    CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS conversations (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, value TEXT);\\n    34→    CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS conversations_v2 (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, value TEXT, updated_at TEXT);\\n    35→    CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS history (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY, value TEXT, updated_at TEXT);\\n    36→    SQL\\n    37→    sqlite3 \\\"$DB_PATH\\\" \\\"INSERT OR REPLACE INTO auth_kv (key, value) VALUES ('kirocli:o